{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3090", "repo": "rails", "body": "@Rhywden\r\nIt's work fine, rails 3.1.1 (or rails 3.2.0.beta) with mail 2.3.0 in my environment.\r\nI found reproduce way.\r\n\r\nI used New API. For example\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\n...\r\ndef send_email\r\n  mail(:to => 'foo@bar.com',\r\n        :subject => 'a subject')\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\nDid you use the Old API?  For example\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\n...\r\ndef send_email\r\n  subject \"a subject\"\r\n  recipients \"foo@bar.com\"\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think that Old API had the bug.\r\nPlease see https://github.com/rails/rails/blob/3-1-stable/actionmailer/lib/action_mailer/old_api.rb#L210\r\nAnd, I recognize that Old API will be removed in rails 3.2.", "_id": {"$oid": "523836f5bd3543c15100fddc"}, "issue_id": 3090, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2458448", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3090#issuecomment-2458448", "updated_at": "2011-10-19T17:22:18Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj", "login": "kennyj", "gravatar_id": "1f0b221851379759360d7130dabdfa53", "html_url": "https://github.com/kennyj", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/1f0b221851379759360d7130dabdfa53?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F54ecc28e9508fcf28363014b0d1b4eb8.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 13426, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at